video:video.video:description: Rare Gem Talent School in Kenya uses hands-on lessons for students with dyslexia. Despite increased access to public education, students with learning disabilities often struggle.

video:video.video:title: Mark Zuckerberg quizzed on kids' Instagram use in social media trial - AP Explains
video:video.video:description: Mark Zuckerberg appeared in a Los Angeles courtroom where he testified in an unprecedented social media trial that questions whether Meta's platforms deliberately addict and harm children.

video:video.video:title: Founder of Social Media Victims Law Center speaks after Zuckerberg testimony
video:video.video:description: Mark Zuckerberg and opposing lawyers dueled in a Los Angeles courtroom Wednesday as he answered questions about young people’s use of Instagram, his congressional testimony and internal advice he’s received about being “authentic” and not “robotic.”

video:video.video:title: Snow drought helped set the stage for deadly California avalanche, leading to unstable conditions
video:video.video:description: Experts say a weekslong “snow drought” in Norther California's Sierra Nevada helped set the stage for Tuesday's deadly avalanche, after several feet of new snow fell on an earlier layer that had hardened.

video:video.video:title: Ukrainian skeleton racer banned from Winter Olympics gives interview on return to Kyiv
video:video.video:description: After being disqualified from the Milan Cortina Olympics, Ukrainian skeleton racer Vladyslav Heraskevych returned to Kyiv to find his capital suffering disruptions of power, heating and water.

video:video.video:title: Family’s GoFundMe journey fuels Laila Edwards’ historic Olympic debut as US advances to gold game
video:video.video:description: Before the U.S. women’s ice hockey team faced Sweden Monday, beating them 5-0 and securing a spot in the final where they’ll go for gold, the family of defender Laila Edwards gathered outside Milan’s Santagiulia Ice Hockey Arena.

video:video.video:title: AI helps farmers in India enhance efficiency and increase harvests
video:video.video:description: AI technology may help to transform Indian agriculture, enhancing efficiency and increasing harvests.

video:video.video:title: Hawaii residents sick of early crowing and aggressive pecking could be allowed to kill wild chickens
video:video.video:description: Hawaii lawmakers are weighing tougher ways to deal with feral chickens. (AP Video by Jennifer Kelleher and Audrey McAvoy)

video:video.video:title: Peru's congress elects country's eighth president in a decade
video:video.video:description: Peru’s Congress on Wednesday elected legislator José María Balcázar as the country's eighth president in a decade, replacing another interim leader who was ousted the previous day over corruption allegations just four months into his term.

video:video.video:title: Muslims worldwide begin daily fasting from dawn to sunset as holy month of Ramadan starts
video:video.video:description: Muslims around the world gathered to celebrate Ramadan including Pakistan, Saudi Arabia, Bosnia - Herzegovina and Iraq.

video:video.video:title: Putin tells Cuban foreign minister Russia will not accept recent US sanctions against Cuba
video:video.video:description: Russian President Vladimir Putin met on Wednesday with Cuban Foreign Minister Bruno Rodriguez in Moscow and reaffirmed his support for the island nation.
